The paper focuses on explaining the predictions of Deep Learning models in the domain of text classification, specifically using Layer-wise Relevance Propagation (LRP) and saliency maps. This falls under the sub-category of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Machine Learning (ML), which are covered by cs.CL and cs.LG respectively. The paper also discusses feature-based evaluation and perturbations, which are common topics in the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Computer Vision (cs.CV).
